    I have many tricks up the sleeves of my T-shirt. :-)

75. The spool will now handle 'user disconnections' (carrier loss etc)
    properly.

76. Amazing how much redundancy there is... The 'SourceCode' I work
    with is currently 146578 bytes, and the distribution copy is
    about a third of that - at only 61327 bytes... :-)
 
77. NOTE: The WimpSlot has been lowered to 128K. If SysOpChat gives 
          you ANY problems or erratic bahavior, raise the WimpSlot to
          160K.

78. It's 03:30h. I've been at this for three or so hours. Night night...


Added in beta17:

**. Nothing, just trying out a few ideas here.


Added in beta18:

79. BIG HELLO TO CHRIS JACKSON... I READ YOUR HELP FILE. :-)))

80. In Alt-spool (full screen) mode, the 1stWord+ decoder will attempt to add
    in Faint (light), Bold, Italic and Underline codes. I think I've got most
    (each combination is cumulative, not additional!). It may screw up
    totally however... Let me know...
    There's a file supplied in SysOpChat somewhere called 'CodeTest'. Use this
    to see. Note, ArcBBS and ArcTerm don't support italics/underline/faint
    properly.

81. I've created a generic ASCII output routine that will dump out plain 
    ASCII (CHR$32 to CHR$127). This method is currently selected for all
    previously undefined filetypes...

82. Each character is 'assessed', so the dodgy cursor bits will
    now not happen - unless you press a cursor or TAB (these are
    'handled' by the Wimp... Hmmm).

83. Now changed to be a RiscOS 3.10 task (passes 310 to Wimp).

84. 'Nice templates' option. This will use the templates "NiceTempls" instead
    of the regular ones. Note that the 'outline font use in the nice templates
    is prone to messing up as there is no extended redrawing facility. It is
    there just to give you an idea, and let you play around with the 
    templates.

85. SysOpChat is now internationalised. Most (if not all) non-template is read
    in from the appropriate messages file.
    Please DO NOT alter the messages files, as a lot of things are 
    space-critical.

86. Redone message file to use RMA - and release it again after... :-)

87. Message language set up for UK, Spain, France, Sweden and Germany. All of
    the message files contain English text at the moment, I've not attempted
    any form of translation.
    Well... Tell a lie... About 1/4 of "Spain" has been translated.


Added in beta20:

88. Changed position of messages, and made templates also internationalisable.

89. Allowed for basic customisation of screens and colours.

90. Added a section on customisation in the instructions. Let's see some
    ideas!

91. Removed colour from VT100/standardASCII modes.

92. Changed all remaining "ESC[##;##f" commands to use "ESC[##;##H".


Added in beta21:

93. If time remaining is <1 and ArmBBS mode is set, take time to be 
    unrestricted. This will probably screw up drop-user settings less than
    1 minute - but <1 is silly anyhow... You should leave time for the user
    to log off properly.

94. "Timer disabled" now fixed, though this should now be superfluous as
    ArmBBSs timer works properly now.


Added in beta22:

95. Special config spool-to-user function now forces full screen spooling for
    speed.

96. Redraw routines will now work whilst spooling in a chat (ie: not the full
    screen spool). It'll be slow and chaotic - but you should really hold
    down ALT when dragging a file in. Full-screen is much neater.

97. Fixed lack of ":" in spooled chat.

98. Forcechat now works for ArmBBS. You must still use the ArmBBS selection
    as things can go badly wrong if you try to read user's address (ain't none
    in ArmBBS!).

99. Waaahhhh it's hot!

00. A century of bug fixes and additions! Erk!

01. 'German' resources are now called 'Germany'.

02. The ForceChat display is now auto-updating, once every 15 polls (about 2/3
    second with BBS running).

